Question: Do you think standard tests accurately assess student abilities?
Answer:
I think they can get within the general region. As in, the tests hqve the potential to operate that way with the vast majority of students. But there are always exceptions. We live in a time when school districts are willing to give each student an individualized education plan or IEP. But still the government expects that every student take the same test and measure them objectively in relation to all other students. There is a disparity there. So ultimately, I think that the tests do not accurately assess students abilities.